cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a neural network model for learning document representations for NLP tasks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The model uses distributed representations, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The goal of the model is to preserve key semantics of the input text, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model is evaluated on document understanding tasks, which can involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV).
